value.name: Message
value.value:
Hello, my name is CitBot. I can recommend papers, search papers based on keywords and manage a paper list for you.
- Send me "!rec <citation context>". I will find some related papers for the context based on their semantics. Please keep in mind that I only compare the context with the titles and abstracts of the papers in my dataset, so send me a sentence that summarizes the paper you want to find would lead to a better recommendation. In the result message, you can add papers to your marking list, where you can generate a BibTeX document for these papers.
- Send me "!kw <keywords>". I will find some papers containing the keywords in their title. Here you can also add papers to your marking list, where you can generate a BibTeX document for these papers. To find a specific paper with some proper nouns, I strongly recommend you to search them by keywords, instead of using !rec command.
- Send me "!list". I will send you the marking list, where you can find all the papers you have marked, and get the BibTeX document by clicking the "Generate BibTex" button.
- If you found some papers in the result message are with wrong information, you can send feedback by clicking the "Feedback" button in the result message. After clicking the "Feedback" button, a window will pop up, where you can write down the feedback. Moreover, if you have other suggestions, you can also write them in the feedback window. I am glad to receive your feedback and make myself more powerful.
